==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Greeve
<hw>Greeve</hw></mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>ger⟦emac⟧fa</ets>. Cf. <er>Reeve</er> an
officer.]</ety> <def>A manager of a farm, or overseer of any work; a
reeve; a manorial bailiff.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their children were horsewhipped by the <qex>grieve</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grieve</ent>⟦br⟧
